From 2790ca35ba6f073422e919006b09c8b7a65a59cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Nov 2025 18:15:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:hostapd: WPS:Add support for WPA2 and WPA3 when
 sta is configured using WPS

When station is configured using WPS, the encryption mode is updated to
wireless config using ubus, though encryption received is PSK2 update it
as sae-mixed so that it can connect with both WPA2 and WPA3 AP vap on
reboot.

Signed-off-by: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 wpa_supplicant/ubus.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/wpa_supplicant/ubus.c b/wpa_supplicant/ubus.c
index 0720eef..8dec7c2 100644
--- a/wpa_supplicant/ubus.c
+++ b/wpa_supplicant/ubus.c
@@ -249,7 +249,7 @@ void wpas_ubus_notify(struct wpa_supplicant *wpa_s, const struct wps_credential
 
 	switch (auth_type) {
 		case WPS_AUTH_WPA2PSK:
-			encryption = "psk2";
+			encryption = "sae-mixed";
 			break;
 		case WPS_AUTH_WPAPSK:
 			encryption = "psk";
-- 
2.34.1

